<HEADLINE>
<P>
DINO VALENTI; LEAD SINGER OF QUICKSILVER MESSENGER SERVICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dino Valenti, 57, songwriter and lead singer of Quicksilver Messenger 
Service.Valenti's real name was Chester Powers. He joined the band in 1964 and 
again in 1970, remaining until 1979. He had dropped out in the 1960s because of 
drug charges and imprisonment and a try at a solo career. Among the songs he 
wrote were "Get Together," which was recorded by the Youngbloods, and "What 
About Me." On Wednesday in Santa Rosa of unknown causes. 
</P>
