<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO AUTHENTIC CHRISTIAN WORSHIP AT PLANETARY MASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In reference to "Multimedia Missionaries" (Nov. 5), Richard C. Paddock's 
restrained review of the Planetary Mass at Grace Cathedral, Paddock notes that 
Jerry Garcia of the Grateful Dead attended the service. As one of the 
attendees, we were beamed back to the '60s via vintage Roberta Flack, 
psychedelic lights, the distribution of flowers, and we were urged to "break 
out through," reminiscent of the Doors. 
</P>
<P>
 Jesus was seldom heard. 
</P>
<P>
 The Planetary Mass represents the demise of authentic Christian worship; a mix 
of Christian mysticism, Eastern spiritualism, Native American religions, 
feminism and environmentalism resulting in witchcraft, paganism and a trendy 
experience. 
</P>
<P>
 Rave Masses are already passe in England, where they originated. Laughing 
services are all the rage. What's next? 
</P>
<P>
 TERI SEIPEL 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside 
</P>
</TEXT>
