<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BATTLE FOR NO. 1 BEING FOUGHT ON PAPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Penn State's fourth-quarter comeback last Saturday not only earned it a 
victory over Illinois, it probably ensured a national championship. How? Miami 
tops undefeated Nebraska in the Orange Bowl and Florida State edges undefeated 
Alabama in the Sugar Bowl, leaving Penn State as the only remaining undefeated 
and untied team.And who ever heard of a duck beating a lion? 
</P>
<P>
 ROSS NINBERGER 
</P>
<P>
 Marina del Rey 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 As an attorney, allow me to present the evidence in support of ranking 
Nebraska No. 2 in the nation: The Cornhuskers are 10-0, they limited 
then-undefeated Kansas State to six points, they shut out mighty Colorado for a 
half and then gave up only seven points, all of this "without a quarterback." 
</P>
<P>
 Something tells me this is a losing argument. 
</P>
<P>
 DOUGLAS F. FAGAN 
</P>
<P>
 Ontario 
</P>
</TEXT>
