<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New World Communications Names President: Arthur Bilger, who helped run Drexel 
Burnham Lambert's corporate finance department in the 1980s, will also take 
over as chief operating officer of the company. William C. Bevins remains chief 
executive of New World, which is controlled by financier Ronald O. Perelman. 
Bilger most recently was a partner at Apollo Advisors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
