<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROPOSITION 187 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If France, Germany, Italy and Mexico were to simultaneously decide that they 
could no longer afford to provide for the education, health and welfare of 
non-citizens living within its borders, would we as Americans protest? 
</P>
<P>
 Of course not; in fact, we might even congratulate them on a fiscally sound 
and reasonable move. 
</P>
<P>
 This shows just how asinine the rest of the world is (with some of our own 
residents included) to take offense with California's belated attempt, via 
Proposition 187, at sane money management and common sense. 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT SHAVELLE 
</P>
<P>
 Brea 
</P>
