<HEADLINE>
<P>
AROMATHERAPY DIRECTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A partial list of emotional and physical imbalances that aromatherapy is said 
to help, according to "Rejuvenation: A Wellness Guide for Men and Women," by 
Horst Rechelbacher: 
</P>
<P>
 * Low energy: basil, cinnamon, clove, garlic, geranium, hyssop, marjoram, 
nutmeg. 
</P>
<P>
 * Indigestion: aniseed, basil, bergamot, chamomile, cinnamon, clove, fennel, 
garlic, lavender, nutmeg, peppermint, thyme. 
</P>
<P>
 * Anxiety: basil, chamomile, eucalyptus, jasmine, marjoram, motti, neroli, 
rose, thyme, ylang-ylang. 
</P>
<P>
 * Headache: chamomile, cardamom, lavender, lemon, motti, peppermint, rosemary, 
wintergreen. 
</P>
<P>
 * Insect bites: basil, cinnamon, garlic, lavender, lemon, sage, savory, thyme. 
</P>
<P>
 * Stress or fatigue: basil, chamomile, cinnamon, clove, cypress, frankincense, 
genet, jasmine, lavender, marjoram, motti, neroli, orange, rose, sage, savory, 
sandalwood, thyme, vanilla. 
</P>
<P>
 * Menstrual cramps: aniseed, cajeput, chamomile, clary sage, cypress, 
eucalyptus, juniper, marjoram, peppermint, rose, rosemary, tarragon, 
ylang-ylang. 
</P>
