<P>
ANOTHER SERIAL KILLER PLAGUES RUSSIAN CITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eight months after the execution of a resident who murdered 52 people, 
authorities in this southern Russian city are searching once again for a serial 
killer. 
</P>
<P>
 Police believe the culprit has already slain eight women in two rural 
districts of the Rostov region, the Itar-Tass news agency reported on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities have not ruled out the possibility that more than one killer is at 
work, said Col. Vasily Kolesnik, the region's chief criminal investigator. 
</P>
<P>
 The city won notoriety as home of the so-called "Rostov Ripper," a former 
teacher and Communist Party member who terrorized the region for 12 years 
before he was arrested in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 Andrei Chikatilo was convicted of murdering, mutilating and cannibalizing 21 
boys, 14 girls and 17 older women. Chikatilo was executed in Rostov-on-Don in 
February. 
