<P>
IRAN GIVES DIVORCED WOMEN PROPERTY RIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A new Iranian law gives some women being divorced by their husbands the right 
to up to half the property accumulated during their married life, Iran's top 
judge said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 While the law is limited in scope, and the actual awards are to be decided by 
a court, the measure could prove a significant advance for women in the face of 
Islamic family laws that give most rights to men. 
</P>
<P>
 Ayatollah Mohammad Yazdi, the chief of the judiciary, said the law was 
designed to protect women whose husbands wanted to leave them for younger 
wives. 
</P>
