<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; MAN GETS 18 YEARS TO LIFE IN SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARBARA MURPHY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Canoga Park man was sentenced Friday to 18 years to life in prison for the 
December shooting death of a Ventura man outside the victim's apartment 
building. 
</P>
<P>
 Garabet Majoubian, 45, received the mandatory sentence of 15 years to life for 
second-degree murder, plus three years for using a gun to commit the crime. 
</P>
<P>
 Majoubian pleaded guilty in Superior Court to second-degree murder in the Dec. 
20 shooting of Erasmo Moro, 48, who worked at a Ventura pizza shop. Moro's body 
was found in the carport of the Scandia Apartments in eastern Ventura after 
residents reported hearing shots. 
</P>
<P>
 At a court hearing in March, police testified that Majoubian and Moro had 
argued over a Simi Valley woman, whom both men considered to be their 
girlfriend. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Majoubian, a construction worker, went to Moro's apartment and 
shot the man after an argument. Investigators later found a 9-millimeter 
semiautomatic pistol in Majoubian's apartment, police testified. BARBARA MURPHY 
</P>
</TEXT>
