COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LOS ALAMITOS; CITY COUNCIL HIRES JANITORIAL SERVICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has hired a Sepulveda maintenance company to provide 
janitorial services at City Hall and other buildings. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members voted unanimously this week to pay Bell Building Maintenance 
Co. $1,210 a month to clean City Hall, the council chambers, engineering and 
finance offices, the restrooms at Laurel Park, and teen and community centers. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell's bid was one-third of the one presented by the only other bidder, Sure 
Shine Janitorial of Fountain Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The contract is effective through June 30, with an option to extend.BERT 
ELJERA 
