COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; HOTEL TO BE CONVERTED INTO HOME FOR SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEN HALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Planning Commission has approved converting a former Ramada Inn into a 
home for senior citizens. 
</P>
<P>
 The vote this week allows Birtcher Senior Properties to convert the former 
110-unit hotel on a 3.6-acre site at 35 Calle de Industrias into a 75-unit home 
for senior citizens.The City Council must still approve an amendment to the 
city zoning code before the project can go forward. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a shame the hotel was not able to succeed, but I think everybody thought 
this is a real good use for the site," said Commissioner Steve Apodaca, who was 
recently elected to the council and will change seats on Dec. 7.  
</P>
<P>
 A Birtcher spokesman told the commission that the hotel would be gutted and 
rebuilt and that prices for the new units would start at $900 a month and go 
up. LEN HALL 
</P>
