<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; CLEAR SKIES, WARMER WEATHER FORECAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The weekend should be a great one for outdoor sports and events, according to 
weather forecasters who predict warmer temperatures and clear skies for Orange 
County through Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Strong winds should continue to buffet the Southland, with gusts of up to 35 
m.p.h. expected. 
</P>
<P>
 Wind advisories are in effect for mountain areas and the San Gabriel and San 
Fernando valleys. 
</P>
<P>
 According to WeatherData Inc., which provides forecasts for The Times, 
temperatures today should reach the lower 70s and not dip below the upper 40s. 
Sunday should be a bit warmer with most of the gusty wind conditions, what 
forecasters describe as a "cool Santa Ana," gone. 
</P>
<P>
 At the beaches, waves are expected to be 3 to 5 feet. 
</P>
<P>
 Forecasters don't expect any rain for the county in the next few days, as 
several storms from the Pacific Ocean will move inland across the Rocky 
Mountains rather than over Southern California. LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
