<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Highway Patrol arrested a man suspected of being a freeway 
flasher at his workplace Friday in Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Scott Murg, 35, of Temecula was booked by the CHP on suspicion of 
indecent exposure after he reportedly pulled alongside a female driver on the 
Artesia Freeway and exposed himself.The woman said the same man had exposed 
himself on the same freeway 10 to 12 times since August. 
</P>
<P>
 CHP Sgt. Paul Golonski said that a driver, one whose front license plate had 
been removed, always exposed himself during afternoon commuter hours on the 
Artesia Freeway or the Corona Freeway in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 Murg, a carpenter, has a 1993 conviction for indecent exposure and two prior 
arrests on similar charges, Golonski said. 
</P>
