<P>
 The following statement was in The Times on Tuesday: "Al LoCasale, executive 
assistant for the Raiders, defended his fans, saying fights are expected any 
time half of the stadium is filled with people rooting against the home team." 
</P>
<P>
 If this is the attitude of Raider management, no wonder there are fights 
wherever the Raider fans go. I have been a Ram season ticket-holder for 24 
years, and I have yet to see the San Diego Charger fans that come en masse to 
Anaheim act like the Raider thugs. Even the Dallas Cowboys and San Francisco 
49ers, which always have many fans and are rowdy and spirited, react nothing 
like the Raider thugs. 
</P>
<P>
 Stay in LA! 
</P>
<P>
