<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: REPORT TO LOOK AT CHARITIES' HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With the holiday season approaching, the Los Angeles Times Valley Edition is 
preparing a special report on the status of charities in the Valley and how 
they have fared after the string of disasters that have struck the region in 
the last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The report, to run next week, will include a listing of many of the 
organizations needing help and donations for the holiday season.Groups that 
want to be included in that list -- especially those that have had a tough time 
this year -- should write to Special Charities Report, Los Angeles Times Valley 
Edition, 20000 Prairie St., Chatsworth 91311 or fax requests to (818) 772-3385. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for listings is noon Tuesday. Listings will run according to 
space availability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
