<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SOUTHERN SECTION PLAYOFFS; DIVISION V; SADDLEBACK TOUGH, BUT 
SAILORS WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AHMED V. ORTIZ, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brian Johnson's 183 rushing yards and two blocked punts by Scott Sandstrom 
carried top-seeded Newport Harbor past stubborn Saddleback, 28-14, in a 
Southern Section Division V first-round playoff game Friday night at Newport 
Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 The undefeated Sailors matched the school record for victories with 11, but it 
wasn't easy. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor surged to a 21-7 halftime lead despite an offense that featured 
Johnson and little else. He rushed for 111 first-half yards, including a 
56-yard score on the game's first play. The rest of the team accounted for 
three yards in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback countered Johnson's score with a 66-yard, 10-play drive, capped by 
Danny Verino's 29-yard run. That gave the Roadrunners a 7-6 lead, but then 
Sandstrom struck, setting up Newport Harbor's next two scores. His first block 
at the end of the first quarter gave the the Sailors the ball at the Roadrunner 
30. After five Johnson runs, Jeremy Mason bulled in from the two. 
</P>
<P>
 On Saddleback's next possession, Sandstrom again stormed over left end for a 
block, this time leaving the offense at the Roadrunner 20. Again, Johnson got 
everything but the score, carrying three times for 15 yards before John 
Giordani connected on a five-yarder to Danny Pulido. 
</P>
<P>
 Danny Rodriguez's eight-yard pass to Jose Roman made things interesting at 
21-14 with nine minutes left, but the Sailors tore downfield and put the game 
away on a seven-yard pass from Giordani to Matt Riggle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
