<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SOUTHERN SECTION PLAYOFFS; DIVISION V; EL TORO ESTABLISHES EARLY 
LEAD, MANAGES TO HOLD OFF SAVANNA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Toro took an 18-point lead in the first half and held on to upset 
second-seeded Savanna, 35-33, in a Division V playoff game Friday night at 
Glover Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro running back Jamie Hanaway scored the eventual winning touchdown on a 
21-yard run with 6 minutes 3 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Next week, El Toro plays the winner of tonight's Canyon-Loara game. 
</P>
<P>
 After Savanna closed to 35-33 on a 33-yard touchdown pass from Jeremy Klemp to 
Edrick Ennis with 4:05 left, Hanaway picked up first downs on two straight 
third and two situations to seal the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Hanaway finished with 154 yards in 24 carries, including 103 in the second 
half. He also caught three passes for 20 yards and a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna (8-3) hurt itself with three turnovers, and committed two crucial 
errors on special teams in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 After Hanaway caught a 13-yard touchdown pass from Brian Wilson to give El 
Toro a 14-10 lead in the second quarter, Savanna's Mike Flores fumbled the 
ensuing kickoff, and Jeremy Jarrett recovered for El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
 Three plays later, Joe Ader scored on a one-yard run to give El Toro a 21-10 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
 After stopping Savanna on its next possession, the Chargers' Mark Gates 
blocked a punt and Jarrett returned it 15 yards to the Rebel one-yard line. 
Wilson then scored on a one-yard run. GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</TEXT>
