<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SOUTHERN SECTION PLAYOFFS; DIVISION VIII; LA MIRADA TAKES 
ADVANTAGE OF UNIVERSITY TURNOVERS TO WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-seeded La Mirada capitalized on seven turnovers to defeat University, 
24-0, in the first round of the Division VIII playoffs Friday night at La 
Mirada High School. 
</P>
<P>
 La Mirada (11-0) was led by Mike Palumbo, who completed 13 of 17 passes for 
126 yards.University quarterback Alan Price completed only four of 12 passes 
for 32 yards with four interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
 University, which finished 4-6-1, also fumbled the ball away three times. 
</P>
<P>
 La Mirada moved out to a 3-0 lead on a 26-yard field goal by Eric Martinez 
with 10 minutes 6 seconds remaining in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadores took a 10-0 lead when Palumbo connected with Wyatt Boatright on 
an 18-yard touchdown pass with 6:38 left in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 La Mirada moved ahead, 17-0, on a two-yard touchdown run by Brett Darnell, 
with 51 seconds left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 La Mirada then took a 24-0 lead when Jeff Nicolini recovered a fumble and 
returned the ball 10 yards for a touchdown with 6:03 left in the fourth 
quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
