<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SOUTHERN SECTION PLAYOFFS; DIVISION X; ORANGE LUTHERAN ROUTS L.A. 
BAPTIST, 56-6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-seeded Orange Lutheran scored on its first four possessions and added an 
interception return for a touchdown to take 35-point lead at halftime and went 
on to a 56-6 victory over Los Angeles Baptist in a Division X playoff game 
Friday at Brea-Olinda High. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran (9-2) dominated the game, rolling up 454 yards in total 
offense against Los Angeles Baptist (3-8), the division's defending champion. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers advance to play Phelan Serrano next week. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran scored on its first possession on a 32-yard pass from 
quarterback Joe Juliano to wide receiver Mike Crawford with 8 minutes 46 
seconds left in the first quarter. The Lancers' next touchdown came when 
running back Che Holloway scored on a 12-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran added its third touchdown of the first quarter when Juliano 
completed a 24-yard scoring pass to Crawford with 46 seconds left in the 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers scored when linebacker Aaron Kenney returned an interception 30 
yards for a touchdown. The score put Orange Lutheran up, 28-0. The final score 
of the half came when Matt Stratton ran into the end zone from two yards with 
3:32 left. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers dominated on the ground thanks to Holloway and Najja Kee. Holloway 
finished with 152 yards in 11 carries. He scored two touchdowns, including one 
from 69 yards in the third quarter. KEN HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
