COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; GOLDEN WEST ADVANCES TO STATE WATER POLO FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden West advanced to the championship game of the State water polo 
tournament by winning twice Friday at Belmont Plaza in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rustlers (27-3) beat Diablo Valley, 14-12, in the semifinals after beating 
West Valley, 17-7, earlier in the quarterfinals. Golden West, the second-ranked 
team in the state, plays top-ranked Long Beach at 3:30 p.m. for the title. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West will be going for its sixth consecutive State title. 
</P>
<P>
 This will be the seventh meeting between the teams this season. They have 
split the first six. 
</P>
<P>
 John Chomin had four goals and Jason Young, Tom Anderson and Ryk Wormgoor had 
three goals each in the victory over Diablo Valley. Matt Braun and Chomin had 
four goals each in the victory over Diablo Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach (25-4) beat Modesto, 24-9, in the quarterfinals, then got past 
Citrus, 12-11, in the other semifinal. 
</P>
