<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: GOLDEN WEST DOMINATES HONORS IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seven Golden West College volleyball players have been selected for the Orange 
Empire Conference all-star teams, and sophomore middle blocker Vanessa Dahl was 
chosen as the conference's most valuable player. 
</P>
<P>
 Dahl had 75 kills and a .420 attack percentage. 
</P>
<P>
 She was joined on the first team by outside hitters Becca Foltz and Christine 
Helms and setter Lemia Astarabadi. Three other Golden West players received 
second-team honors: Jessica Redding, Michelle Wineke and Nicole Mordhorst. 
</P>
<P>
 Other first-team selections were Andrea Bill and Lori Bowers of Saddleback and 
Heather Daze and Heather Ruhl of Orange Coast. 
</P>
<P>
 Other second-team choices were Kelly Gallup of Saddleback, Yuki Inagaki of 
Rancho Santiago, Stephanie Pfeiffer of Fullerton and Amy Wilson of OCC. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Diane Lewis of Long Beach Millikan has been named interim softball coach at 
OCC for the 1995 season. 
</P>
<P>
 She succeeds Nick Trani, who moved to a similar position at Saddleback 
College. A permanent coach will be named in the spring, and Lewis said she 
plans to apply for the position. As a pitcher, Lewis led Millikan to the 
Southern Section 3-A championship in 1983. Trani was Millikan's coach at the 
time. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Doyle, an assistant coach at La Quinta, has been hired as baseball coach 
at Westminster, Athletic Director Stan Clark said. It's his first head coaching 
position. 
</P>
