1992 riots, has received $173,000 from the Jewish Fund for Justice and the 
Liberty Hill, McKay(and Tidesfoundations. The grantee organizations -- 10 
groups that address issues ranging from citizen participation, illiteracy and 
job creation to gang violence and youth leadership -- each received $15,000 to 
$20,000. They work throughout the city, in neighborhoods including 
South-Central and Southeast Los Angeles, Koreatown, Hollywood and Echo Park. 
</P>
