<HEADLINE>
<P>
BELL-JEFF PLAYOFF GAME MOVED BECAUSE OF SNOW AND COLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Snow and cold weather have forced Bell-Jeff's Division X playoff game against 
host Big Bear to be relocated to San Bernardino Aquinas High School at 7 
tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 Three to four inches of snow fell on Big Bear's field during the week and 
school officials could not line the field properly because it had frozen. 
</P>
<P>
 Temperatures have ranged from 12-30 degrees. 
</P>
<P>
 An announcement was made Friday afternoon that the game had been moved. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're not going to be missing the snow, but I assume it will be cold in San 
Bernardino, too," Bell-Jeff Coach Doug Woodlief said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The coaching staff went over a few things with the kids on how to dress. 
They'll need to wear gloves and extra things like that.  
</P>
<P>
 "We're just happy to be in the playoffs." 
</P>
<P>
 The Guards have not been to the playoffs since 1986. 
</P>
<P>
 Aquinas is located about 50 miles from Big Bear. 
</P>
<P>
 It is the second consecutive week that a game has been moved because to 
weather. BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
