<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; DIVISION I 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES TEMMEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Long Beach Jordan 46, Crespi 21 -- After suffering a defeat at the hands of 
Crespi in the first round of last year's playoffs, host Jordan got revenge. 
</P>
<P>
 Jordan (8-3) piled up 628 yards.Junior quarterback Ortege Jenkins threw five 
touchdown passes in the first half and finished with nine completions in 15 
attempts for 279 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Jenkins connected on scoring pass plays of 80, 36, 26, 69 and 43 yards. 
Running back LeJuan Gibbons rushed for 158 yards in 17 carries and caught two 
touchdown passes. 
</P>
<P>
 Crespi quarterback David Lins completed 14 of 29 passes for 205 yards and 
three touchdowns. Lins connected with wide receiver Jeff DeFinney on a 23-yard 
scoring pass in the third quarter for the Celts' first points. 
</P>
<P>
 Lins added scoring passes of 23 and 24 yards to receiver Wayne Emerson, who 
finished with eight catches for 125 yards. With his 205-yard passing effort, 
Lins finished the year with 2,088 yards to break the school record for 
single-season passing yardage set in 1991 by Cody Smith. JAMES TEMMEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
