<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; DIVISION II 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE GALLUZZO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saugus 35, Pasadena 32 -- Saugus and Pasadena combined for five fourth-quarter 
touchdowns as the Centurions won a thriller at Canyon High. 
</P>
<P>
 Colin Butterfield intercepted a pass by Pasadena quarterback Chris McAlister 
at the Saugus 33-yard line with 32 seconds to play to seal the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Butterfield also scored two touchdowns for Saugus (6-3-1), including the 
game-winner on an eight-yard run with 1:29 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeremy Mushinski rushed for 165 yards and two touchdowns in 19 carries for 
Saugus. 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena (8-3) was led by Koran Allen, who rushed for 146 yards and two 
touchdowns in 14 carries. Allen's 16-yard touchdown reception put Pasadena 
ahead, 21-20, with 11:09 to play. STEVE GALLUZZO 
</P>
