<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL PLAYOFF ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 24, Dominguez 7 -- Big plays and a stingy defense keyed 
third-seeded Antelope Valley's victory at home.After a slow start, the 
Antelopes (8-2) got going when defensive lineman Jared Westberg picked up a 
fumble and ran 68 yards for a touchdown, which cut the Dons' lead to 7-6 midway 
through the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Following a missed field goal, Jermaine Lewis capped an 80-yard drive with a 
five-yard scoring run to put Antelope Valley ahead to stay, 13-7. Lewis 
finished with 59 yards in 18 carries, and his 83-yard kickoff return opened the 
second half and gave the Antelopes a 21-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley plays Saugus in next week's quarterfinals. RON STAPP 
</P>
