<HEADLINE>
<P>
NUCCITELLI CARRIES MONROE, 35-6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nick Nuccitelli rushed for 209 yards in 27 carries and scored two touchdowns 
to lead Monroe High to a 35-6 victory over Gardena on Friday in the first round 
of the City Section 3-A Division playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Nuccitelli, who played in the fourth quarter after suffering a fractured right 
hand, scored on runs of one yard and four yards.His shorter run started a 
decisive 21-point second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 He has 1,642 yards rushing this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Jesse Jones of Monroe (6-5) rushed for 134 yards in 16 carries and scored 
twice. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings, who lead the area in rushing, amassed 437 yards on the ground. 
They threw only one pass in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 For Gardena (3-7-1), Ray Madden gained 63 yards in 11 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 In Wednesday's quarterfinals, Monroe will play Birmingham, which defeated 
Reseda, 22-6. ALAN SPRINGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
