<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; GRANADA HILLS PASSING GAME FIRES BLANKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER YOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The usually potent passing attack of Granada Hills High never got untracked 
Friday night as the Highlanders fell, 14-0, to Dorsey in the first round of the 
City Section 4-A Division playoffs at Jackie Robinson Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Granada Hills quarterback Brian MacLean, who averaged more than 200 yards 
passing a game during the regular season, completed six of 26 passes for 81 
yards and had three interceptions.The Highlanders (6-4-1) managed only two 
first downs and 63 total yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Both touchdowns for Dorsey (9-2) came after interceptions deep in Granada 
Hills territory. John Watkins intercepted MacLean's pass in the second quarter 
at the Highlander 34 and returned it 24 yards.  
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Roderick Brown's subsequent one-yard bootleg gave Dorsey a 7-0 
halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Late in the third quarter, linebacker Juan Jimenez picked off MacLean's pass 
at the Granada Hills 20. Three plays later Antwain Wilson scored from one yard. 
PETER YOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
