<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / PRESEASON NIT; OHIO KNOCKS OFF NO. 14 VIRGINIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gary Trent had 20 points and 13 rebounds Friday night as Ohio University 
scored a 94-83 victory over 14th-ranked Virginia in the second round of the 
Preseason NIT at Charlottesville, Va. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bobcats (2-0) were leading, 76-56, with 6:48 left, when Virginia (1-1) 
rallied. 
</P>
<P>
 At Washington, Kwame Evans scored 13 points and Nimbo Hammons and Antoine Hart 
had 12 each as George Washington reached the semifinals with a 62-59 victory 
over Canisius. Evans, Hammons and Hart were among five double-figure scorers 
for George Washington. The Colonials (2-0) will face Ohio at New York's Madison 
Square Garden on Wednesday. 
</P>
