<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brad Holland played quarterback on the 1973 Crescenta Valley High football 
team that won the Southern Section 3-A Division championship. Holland, who went 
on to star in basketball at UCLA and play for the Lakers, helped the Falcons 
post a 12-1 record. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley defeated Monrovia, 14-7, in the final after posting playoff 
victories of 25-0 over Pomona, 35-8 over Thousand Oaks and 34-19 over St. John 
Bosco. 
</P>
</TEXT>
