<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. BAPTIST'S SEASON LACKS ONLY THAT PERFECT ENDING; VOLLEYBALL: KNIGHTS PUT 
19-0 RECORD ON THE LINE IN SOUTHERN SECTION DIVISION V FINAL AGAINST BRENTWOOD. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LAZARUS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 From the beginning of the season, L.A. Baptist High Coach Sue Newcomb expected 
her girls' volleyball team to make the Southern Section Division V final. 
</P>
<P>
 She didn't expect the Knights to have an undefeated season. 
</P>
<P>
 Now, second-seeded L.A. Baptist (19-0) will face by far its toughest test of 
the season against Brentwood at 1 p.m. today at Cypress College. 
</P>
<P>
 Top-seeded Brentwood (17-1) is defending Division V state champion and played 
a demanding schedule against several higher-division powers, including and 
Calvary Chapel, top-seeded in Division IV, and Harvard-Westlake. Brentwood's 
only loss was to La Mirada early in the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitters Kelly Gentile and Katherine Kuchenbecker, middle blocker Erin 
Hawkins and setter Sarah Neal lead the Eagles. 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitter Darcie Frazier has 94 kills over 14 games in four playoff 
matches for L.A. Baptist, many on passes from setter Tundo Hrotko. 
</P>
</TEXT>
