<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; NORTHRIDGE VOLLEYBALL WIN STREAK HITS 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Missy Clements had 18 kills and Heather Anderson added 11 kills and 14 digs as 
visiting Cal State Northridge defeated Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, 15-5, 16-14, 
15-7, in a nonconference women's volleyball match Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the fourth in a row for Northridge (16-8) and the sixth in 
seven matches. The Matadors have swept their opponents in each victory during 
that stretch. 
</P>
<P>
 Clements, a 5-foot-11 outside hitter who had become Northridge's career kill 
leader in the previous match, had a .469 hitting percentage for the Matadors, 
who hit .278 as a team. 
</P>
<P>
 Middle blocker Ana Kristich had five kills and a match-high seven blocks for 
Northridge, which plays at Cal State Sacramento in a regular-season finale 
tonight. MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran 83, UC Santa Cruz 52 -- Derrick Clark had 18 points and seven 
rebounds as Cal Lutheran opened the season with a runaway victory in the first 
round of the Menlo College tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Clark, who was All-Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference 
last season, made seven of 14 shots and all four of his free throws. 
</P>
<P>
 Jon Rider had 11 points, and Dave Ulloa and Christian Dunbar each had 10 for 
the Kingsmen, who will play the winner of Friday's late Occidental-Menlo game 
for the championship tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 61, Rio Hondo 56 -- The Vaqueros shot 60% in the first half and built 
a 21-point lead, but made just six of 24 shots in the second half and held on 
for a nonconference victory at home.  
</P>
<P>
 Maurice McIntosh led Glendale (3-0) with 16 points, Charlie Garcia had 12 
points and 10 rebounds, and Maurice Sowells added 11 points and five assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Victor Valley 95, Valley 84 -- Victor Valley broke open a close game by 
converting free throws down the stretch to hand Valley its first loss in a 
nonconference game at Victor Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Kenyth Henry had 23 points and eight rebounds and guard Craig Griffin had 15 
points for Valley (3-1), which trailed, 40-38, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Point guard Vernard Harris had eight assists for the Monarchs. Victor Valley 
is 2-1. WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Pt. Loma Nazarene 77, The Master's 49 -- Jodi Agueda had 16 points and nine 
rebounds for Master's in the nonconference game at Pt. Loma Nazarene, but the 
Mustangs (1-1) could not recover from 40-14 halftime deficit. 
</P>
<P>
 Connie Van Wingerden added 10 points and four steals for Master's. 
</P>
<P>
 College of the Canyons 87, Compton 71 -- Rebekah Cunnan had 31 points and 14 
rebounds to lead the Cougars in the first round of the Mt. San Jacinto 
Tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Kyetra Brown had 12 rebounds and 12 assists to go along with nine points for 
Canyons (2-0), which built a 35-22 halftime lead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
