<P>
 COACH: Marcia Foster 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 39-33 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Amanda 
Hall Sr. 5-7 G Gina Huizar Jr. 5-8 F Sara Monsoor Jr. 5-8 F Natalee Patterson 
Sr. 5-10 F Janine Shaw Sr. 5-7 G 04,15,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Lorrie 
Duran Jr. 5-8 F Amber Zarndt Sr. 5-6 G 04,15,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P 
April Boose Jr. 5-6 G Kathy Moore So. 6-2 C OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Foster thinks that the key to a successful season lies in the Argonauts seven 
returning players. Some of the Argonauts' strength will come from junior 
varsity players--Moore and Boose--stepping up. Foster said Moore (6-2) will add 
strength inside and should be helpful on the boards. Foster is also hoping 
Shaw, who at guard averaged 10 points and was first-team all-league selection 
last season, will provide strong leadership and scoring. Patterson, who was a 
second-team all-league pick, will also contribute at forward, where she 
averaged seven points. Foster thinks the Argonauts could have a high-scoring 
offense, but whether anyone can fill the scoring hole left by the graduation of 
last year's ace, Michol Murray, remains to be seen. And though Foster 
acknowledges that Garden Grove might be a favorite this year, she is quick to 
point out that there are other good teams in the league, including Santiago and 
Pacifica. But unlike last season, when inexperience was a big factor, Foster is 
counting on experience and team unity. 
</P>
<P>
 SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
