<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995: GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pacifica 1993-94 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 9-14 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 5-9 COACH: Ryan Bettencourt 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 0-0 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Heather 
Green So. 5-9 G Brandi Jones Sr. 5-7 G Erin Kiyomura Jr. 5-5 G Holly Pawlowski 
Sr. 6-0 F 04,15,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Kim Gilley Sr. 5-4 G Amy 
Rummel Sr. 6-0 C 04,15,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Natalie Hupf Jr. 5-7 G 
OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Bettencourt hopes he can bring a little stability to Pacifica. Last year, the 
team finished sixth after finishing as undefeated league champions in 1992-93. 
But there's hope for Bettencourt, who says the team has some good size and 
enough varsity experience to make the Mariners competitive. While first-team 
all-league selection Pilar Surch will be missed, Bettencourt hopes he'll get 
good performances from returning starters Kiyomura, Pawlowski, Jones and Green. 
He's also counting on Hupf, a transfer from Long Beach St. Anthony, who will 
probably play guard. Also expected to contribute is Pawlowski at forward and 
center and Gilley at guard. Though Bettencourt has only been with the team 
since October and has been busy preparing for the season, he still thinks he 
can develop the team's style and be ready for league play in January. 
Bettencourt thinks Garden Grove and Rancho Alamitos will be the teams to beat, 
but that the Mariners can keep up with the rest of the league. "The team has 
talent," Bettencourt said. "It now needs to develop the confidence and a belief 
that it can go to the playoffs." 
</P>
<P>
 SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 November 30 vs. Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
