<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos 1993-94 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 21-7 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 13-1 COACH: Peter Pyle 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 21-7 RETURNING STARTERS: None 04,15,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS 
YR. HGT. P Leena Bhakta Sr. 5-4 G Jamie Howard Sr. 5-9 F Detra Vickers Sr. 5-6 
F 04,19,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Tu Doan Jr. 5-2 G Kristyn Hennes So. 
5-7 F Araceli Hernandez So. 5-10 C Melissa Loera Jr. 5-7 F Wendy Lopez Jr. 5-4 
G Mai-Linh Mainor Sr. 5-5 G Ha Nguyen So. 5-8 F Nguyet Nguyen Jr. 5-8 F OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Attempting to win his fifth consecutive league title, Pyle is optimistic about 
this season despite not having any returning starters. With plenty of speed and 
strong outside shooting, Pyle is counting on Vickers and Howard to lead the way 
in points and leadership. Pyle thinks Lopez, a junior, is ready to step up a 
level and run the offense. He also looks at his nine-deep roster to be another 
contributing factor. With the junior varsity team finishing 14-0 last season, 
he's confident they will be able to fill the gap created by the nine graduated 
seniors. For the first time in seven years, Pyle said there does not appear to 
be a clear-cut league favorite or marquee player. Though he listed his team 
among the favorites, he thinks nearly every team has a chance for the league 
title. "We've had a lot of transfers in the league this year and that balances 
the league outlook," Pyle said. 
</P>
<P>
 SCHEDULE 
</P>
