 OVERALL: 2-20 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 1-13 COACH: Mike Loftis 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 0-0 04,19,05,06,04 RETURNING SARTERS YR. HGT. P Magda Apanol 
Sr. 5-9 G Carmela Zavala Sr. 5-7 G 04,17,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P 
Luanei Esara Sr. 5-8 F Tiffany Nguyen Jr. 5-3 F Bertera Robles Jr. 5-9 C Stacey 
Togatuli Jr. 5-6 G 04,17,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Thua Le Jr. 5-2 G 
Cristina Montes Sr. 5-7 F Truyen Ngo Jr. 5-3 G Andrea Peralta Jr. 5-4 F Janet 
Remaro Jr. 5-5 F Carol Tran Fr. 5-6 F OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Loftis said the Lobos are strong in all areas of the game, and with some good 
players returning, he thinks the ingredients for a winning season are there. 
"Our main goal is to put Los Amigos on the map for working hard and never 
quitting," he said. "And if we get the wins, well, that's just icing on the 
cake." Back at guard is first-team, all-league selection Zavala, who averaged 
16 points and is being counted on as one of the team leaders. Also returning is 
Nguyen, a good shooting guard. Loftis says because there doesn't seem to be one 
dominate team in league this season, it might be a good year for Los Amigos to 
make a statement. But the coach knows if any gain is to be made, it will 
require hard work and dedication. "Our success will depend on how hard we work 
and our attitude on and off the court," Loftis said. "For us, every team and 
every game will be a big game." 
</P>
